quran[40]{c,v,t}:
  75,1,I swear by the Day of Resurrection
  75,2,and I swear by the self reproaching soul
  75,3,Does man think that We shall not be able to put his bones together
  75,4,"Why not? We are able to put together, in perfect order, the very tips of his fingers"
  75,5,But man wishes to keep on doing evil in the future as well
  75,6,"He questions: \"When will this Day of Resurrection be"
  75,7,"Well, it will come when the sight shall be dazed"
  75,8,the moon will be eclipsed
  75,9,and the sun and the moon will be brought together
  75,10,"on that Day man will ask: \"Is there any way to escape"
  75,11,Nay! There will be no refuge
  75,12,"On that Day, the refuge will only be towards your Lord"
  75,13,"On that Day man shall be told about all his deeds, from the first to the last"
  75,14,"Indeed, man shall bear witness against himself"
  75,15,even though he shall plead with excuses
  75,16,"O Prophet, do not move your tongue too fast to memorize this revelation"
  75,17,"It is Our responsibility to collect it in your memory, and make you recite it"
  75,18,"and when it is recited, to make you follow it"
  75,19,and then it is Our responsibility to explain it
  75,20,"Nay, the fact is that you people love this fleeting life"
  75,21,and are heedless to the Hereafter
  75,22,"On that Day, some faces shall be bright"
  75,23,looking towards their Lord
  75,24,And on that Day some faces shall be gloomy
  75,25,thinking that some backbreaking calamity is about to be inflicted on them
  75,26,"Nay, when a man’s soul is about to leave and reaches to the throat"
  75,27,"and those around him cry: \"Is there any enchanter to help"
  75,28,Then man will conclude that it was the time of departure from this world
  75,29,while one leg will twist around the other leg (agony will heap on agony)
  75,30,that will be the Day of driving towards your Lord
  75,31,"But in this life he neither believed, nor offered Salah (prayed)"
  75,32,but on the contrary he denied the truth and turned away
  75,33,Then he went to his kinfolk elated with pride
  75,34,"Woe to you, O man! Woe to you"
  75,35,"Again woe to you, O man! Woe to you"
  75,36,Does man think that he will be left without any purpose
  75,37,Was he not once a drop of emitted semen
  75,38,"Then he became a leechlike mass, then Allah created him and fashioned him in due proportion"
  75,39,"and made him either of the two sexes, male and female"
  75,40,Has He not then the power to bring the dead to life